@startuml MaxHype Architecture
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

title MaxHype - Application Architecture

package "UI Layer" #E3F2FD {
  component [HomeScreen] as Screen
  component [WorkoutCardsScroll] as Cards
  component [MonthlyCalendar] as Calendar
  component [MonthlyHistoryScroll] as History
  component [MonthlyChart] as Chart
  component [WorkoutCard] as Card
}

package "BLoC Layer" #FFF3E0 {
  component [HomeBloc] as Bloc
  component [HomeEvent] as Event
  component [HomeState] as State
}

package "Repository Layer" #F1F8E9 {
  interface "WorkoutRepository" as IRepo <<interface>>
  component [MockWorkoutRepository] as MockRepo
}

package "Data Layer" #FCE4EC {
  component [MockData] as Data
  component [Models:\nWorkout\nMonthlyData\nDailyData] as Models
}

package "Dependency Injection" #EDE7F6 {
  component [GetIt\nServiceLocator] as DI
  component [BlocFactory] as Factory
}

' Relationships
Screen -down-> Bloc : BlocProvider
Bloc -up-> Event : receives
Bloc -up-> State : emits
Screen -up-> State : BlocBuilder\nrebuilds on state
Screen -down-> Cards : contains
Screen -down-> Calendar : contains
Screen -down-> History : contains
History -down-> Chart : contains (2x)
Cards -down-> Card : contains (3x)

Bloc -down-> IRepo : getWorkouts()\ngetMonthlyData()
IRepo <|.down. MockRepo : implements
MockRepo -down-> Data : uses
Data -down-> Models : creates

DI -right-> MockRepo : registers as\nLazySingleton
DI -right-> Factory : registers as\nLazySingleton
Factory -up-> Bloc : creates new\ninstance

' Notes
note right of History
  **PageView Scaling**
  • Handles any number of months
  • Only renders visible + adjacent pages
  • O(1) performance per month
  • Memory: ~3 KB per month
end note

note right of Calendar
  **Calendar Grid**
  • O(weeks) rendering
  • Max ~35 cells per month
  • Dynamic week calculation
  • Color-coded workout days
end note

note right of MockRepo
  **Easy Backend Swap**
  Replace MockWorkoutRepository
  with ApiWorkoutRepository

  No UI changes needed!
end note

note left of Bloc
  **Unidirectional Data Flow**
  1. UI dispatches Event
  2. BLoC processes via Repository
  3. BLoC emits new State
  4. UI rebuilds automatically
end note

note bottom of Models
  **MonthlyData Structure**
  • monthName, year
  • dailyData: List<DailyData>
  • completionPercentage
  • totalKcal

  **DailyData Structure**
  • day, kcal, volume
  • isWorkoutDay
end note

@enduml
